01:31:09,386 --> 01:31:10,762
The.

764
01:31:17,269 --> 01:31:18,270
The.

765
01:32:24,044 --> 01:32:27,631
- No letter?
- No letter. Sign.

766
01:33:55,803 --> 01:33:59,807
- You're Michael Berg?
- Yes.

767
01:33:59,890 --> 01:34:04,436
Thank you for calling me.
You got my letter?

768
01:34:04,520 --> 01:34:06,063
I have it here.

769
01:34:06,146 --> 01:34:10,067
As I say, Hanna Schmitz
is coming up for release very soon.

770
01:34:10,150 --> 01:34:14,196
Hanna has been in prison
for over 20 years.

771
01:34:14,279 --> 01:34:15,322
She has no family.

772
01:34:15,405 --> 01:34:18,283
She has no friends.

773
01:34:18,367 --> 01:34:20,828
You're her only contact.

774
01:34:20,911 --> 01:34:24,164
And I'm told you don't visit her.

775
01:34:24,248 --> 01:34:25,958
No, I don't.

776
01:34:26,041 --> 01:34:28,377
When she gets out,
she's going to need a job.

777
01:34:28,460 --> 01:34:30,838
She's going to need somewhere to live.

778
01:34:30,921 --> 01:34:35,217
You can't imagine how frightening
the modern world will seem to her.

779
01:34:38,637 --> 01:34:39,721
Mm-hmm.

780
01:34:43,433 --> 01:34:45,018
I have no one else to ask.

781
01:34:46,395 --> 01:34:49,273
If you don't take
responsibility for her,

782
01:34:49,356 --> 01:34:51,984
then Hanna has no future at all.

783
01:34:55,404 --> 01:34:57,573
It's kind of you.

784
01:34:57,656 --> 01:34:59,950
Thank you for letting me know.

785
01:35:43,827 --> 01:35:45,496
- You're Michael Berg?
- Yes.

786
01:35:45,579 --> 01:35:47,539
I'm Louisa Brenner. Good morning.

787
01:35:47,623 --> 01:35:51,043
- How do you do?
- We were expecting you earlier.

788
01:35:51,126 --> 01:35:55,214
I should warn you, for a long time
Hanna held herself together.

789
01:35:55,297 --> 01:35:59,301
She was very purposeful. In the
last few years, she's different.

790
01:35:59,384 --> 01:36:01,595
She's let herself go.

791
01:36:04,640 --> 01:36:07,684
I'm taking you straight to the canteen.

792
01:36:09,019 --> 01:36:11,188
They've just finished their lunch.

793
01:36:23,200 --> 01:36:25,202
Table four.

794
01:37:10,706 --> 01:37:13,041
You've grown up, kid.

795
01:37:27,389 --> 01:37:29,391
I've got a friend who's a tailor.

796
01:37:32,561 --> 01:37:33,937
He'll give you a job.

797
01:37:35,939 --> 01:37:39,276
And I've found you somewhere to live.
It's a nice place.

798
01:37:39,359 --> 01:37:40,944
Quite small, but it's nice.

799
01:37:42,529 --> 01:37:44,948
- You'll like it.
- Thank you.

800
01:37:46,783 --> 01:37:51,830
There are various social programs,
cultural stuff I can sign you up for.

801
01:37:51,914 --> 01:37:54,625
And the public library is very close.

802
01:38:01,089 --> 01:38:02,382
You read a lot?

803
01:38:05,302 --> 01:38:07,971
I prefer being read to.

804
01:38:12,601 --> 01:38:14,478
That's over now, isn't it?

805
01:38:24,154 --> 01:38:26,240
Did you get married?

806
01:38:26,323 --> 01:38:29,409
I did. Yes, I did.

807
01:38:29,493 --> 01:38:31,578
We have a daughter.

808
01:38:31,662 --> 01:38:35,082
I'm not seeing as much of her
as I'd like.

809
01:38:35,165 --> 01:38:37,668
I'd like to see
a great deal more of her.

810
01:38:39,920 --> 01:38:42,005
The marriage didn't last.

811
01:38:57,437 --> 01:38:59,898
Have you spent time
thinking about the past?

812
01:38:59,982 --> 01:39:03,777
- You mean with you?
- No.

813
01:39:03,861 --> 01:39:07,573
No, I didn't mean with me.

814
01:39:17,040 --> 01:39:20,794
Before the trial,
I never thought about the past.

815
01:39:20,878 --> 01:39:23,046
I never had to.

816
01:39:23,130 --> 01:39:25,382
Now?

817
01:39:26,675 --> 01:39:28,093
What do you feel now?

818
01:39:29,845 --> 01:39:32,181
It doesn't matter what I feel.

819
01:39:33,182 --> 01:39:35,309
It doesn't matter what I think.

820
01:39:37,394 --> 01:39:39,229
The dead are still dead.

821
01:39:46,737 --> 01:39:48,655
I wasn't sure what you'd learned.

822
01:39:48,739 --> 01:39:52,576
Well, I have learned, kid.

823
01:39:52,659 --> 01:39:55,078
I've learned to read.

824
01:40:08,926 --> 01:40:10,552
I'll pick you up next week, OK?

825
01:40:19,937 --> 01:40:21,897
That sounds a good plan.

826
01:40:24,566 --> 01:40:28,195
We can do it quietly,
or we can make a fuss.

827
01:40:28,278 --> 01:40:30,155
Quietly.

828
01:40:32,157 --> 01:40:34,409
OK. Quietly.

829
01:40:37,120 --> 01:40:38,997
Quietly.

830
01:40:47,631 --> 01:40:51,635
- Take care, kid.
- You, too. See you next week.

831
01:43:04,351 --> 01:43:06,854
I've come to collect Hanna Schmitz.

832
01:43:10,774 --> 01:43:14,027
Please. Please, take a seat.

833
01:43:39,303 --> 01:43:41,930
She didn't pack.

834
01:43:42,014 --> 01:43:44,308
She never intended to leave.

835
01:43:50,063 --> 01:43:53,525
"The talk was that a new face

836
01:43:53,609 --> 01:43:57,196
had appeared on the promenade,

837
01:43:57,279 --> 01:43:59,990
a lady with a little dog. "

838
01:44:06,997 --> 01:44:08,707
She left me a message.

839
01:44:10,626 --> 01:44:12,503
A sort of will.

840
01:44:14,588 --> 01:44:17,508
I'll read the bit that concerns you.

841
01:44:25,307 --> 01:44:28,268
"There is money in the old tea tin.

842
01:44:28,352 --> 01:44:31,104
Give it to Michael Berg.

843
01:44:31,188 --> 01:44:35,859
He should send it,
alongside the 7,000 Marks in the bank,

844
01:44:35,943 --> 01:44:39,738
to the daughter who survived the fire.

845
01:44:39,822 --> 01:44:41,949
It's for her.

846
01:44:42,032 --> 01:44:45,077
She should decide what to do with it.

847
01:44:48,580 --> 01:44:51,416
And tell Michael I said hello. "

848
01:46:09,703 --> 01:46:12,080
- Ms. Mather?
- Yes.

849
01:46:12,790 --> 01:46:14,875
- You're Michael Berg.
- Yes.

850
01:46:14,958 --> 01:46:16,877
I was expecting you.

851
01:46:18,253 --> 01:46:21,924
- Please.
- Thank you.

852
01:46:22,007 --> 01:46:26,470
So you must tell me, exactly what
brings you to the United States?

853
01:46:26,553 --> 01:46:29,640
I was here already.
I was at a conference in Boston.

854
01:46:29,723 --> 01:46:31,016
- You're a lawyer?
- Yes.

855
01:46:31,099 --> 01:46:36,146
I was intrigued by your letter,
but I can't say I wholly understood it.

856
01:46:36,230 --> 01:46:40,234
- You attended the trial?
- Yes. Almost 20 years ago.

857
01:46:40,317 --> 01:46:46,156
I was a law student. I remember you.
I remember your mother very clearly.

858
01:46:46,240 --> 01:46:50,077
My mother died in Israel
a good many years ago.

859
01:46:50,160 --> 01:46:53,580
I... I'm sorry.

860
01:46:53,664 --> 01:46:55,582
Go on, please.

861
01:46:57,459 --> 01:46:59,336
Perhaps you heard.

862
01:46:59,419 --> 01:47:04,216
Hanna Schmitz recently died.
She killed herself.

863
01:47:05,551 --> 01:47:07,010
She was a friend of yours?

864
01:47:08,512 --> 01:47:09,972
A kind of friend.

865
01:47:11,515 --> 01:47:13,517
It's as simple as this.

866
01:47:13,600 --> 01:47:17,938
Hanna was illiterate
for the greater part of her life.

867
01:47:18,021 --> 01:47:21,191
Is that an explanation
of her behavior?

868
01:47:22,901 --> 01:47:25,154
- No.
- Or an excuse?

869
01:47:25,237 --> 01:47:27,364
No. No.

870
01:47:30,409 --> 01:47:34,121
She taught herself to read
when she was in prison.

871
01:47:34,204 --> 01:47:36,874
I sent her tapes.

872
01:47:39,501 --> 01:47:43,380
She had always liked...
being read to.

873
01:47:50,220 --> 01:47:52,973
Why don't you start
by being honest with me?

874
01:47:53,056 --> 01:47:56,101
At least start that way.

875
01:47:56,185 --> 01:47:58,812
What was the nature
of your friendship?

876
01:48:03,734 --> 01:48:06,570
When I was young,
I had an affair with Hanna.

877
01:48:12,493 --> 01:48:14,369
I'm not sure I can help you, Mr. Berg.

878
01:48:14,453 --> 01:48:16,622
And...

879
01:48:16,705 --> 01:48:18,832
...even if I could,
I'm not willing to.

880
01:48:18,916 --> 01:48:21,543
I was almost 16
when I took up with her.

881
01:48:21,627 --> 01:48:24,880
The affair only lasted a summer.
But...

882
01:48:26,423 --> 01:48:28,592
But what?

883
01:48:34,431 --> 01:48:36,141
I see.

884
01:48:38,352 --> 01:48:43,106
And did Hanna Schmitz acknowledge
the effect she'd had on your life?

885
01:48:44,858 --> 01:48:48,195
She'd done much worse
to other people.

886
01:48:53,158 --> 01:48:54,868
I've never told anyone.

887
01:48:59,206 --> 01:49:02,501
People ask all the time
what I learned in the camps.

888
01:49:02,584 --> 01:49:05,295
But the camps weren't therapy.

889
01:49:07,422 --> 01:49:10,134
What do you think these places were,
universities?

890
01:49:11,802 --> 01:49:14,388
We didn't go there to learn.

891
01:49:14,471 --> 01:49:18,517
One becomes very clear
about these things.

892
01:49:21,979 --> 01:49:24,648
What are you asking for?
Forgiveness for her?

893
01:49:24,731 --> 01:49:27,484
Or do you just want
to feel better yourself?

894
01:49:27,568 --> 01:49:31,405
My advice? Go to the theater
if you want catharsis. Please.

895
01:49:31,488 --> 01:49:33,365
Go to literature.

896
01:49:33,448 --> 01:49:36,660
Don't go to the camps.

897
01:49:38,203 --> 01:49:40,664
Nothing comes out of the camps.

898
01:49:43,167 --> 01:49:45,210
Nothing.

899
01:49:58,515 --> 01:50:00,350
What she wanted...

900
01:50:01,268 --> 01:50:05,689
What she wanted was
to leave you her money.

901
01:50:05,772 --> 01:50:08,609
- I have it with me.
- To do what?

902
01:50:10,694 --> 01:50:12,446
As you think fit.

903
01:50:23,457 --> 01:50:25,042
Here.

904
01:50:33,592 --> 01:50:38,388
When I was a little girl,
I had a tea tin for my treasures.

905
01:50:38,472 --> 01:50:42,768
Not quite like this.
It had Cyrillic lettering.

906
01:50:45,646 --> 01:50:48,899
I took it with me to the camp,
but it got stolen.

907
01:50:48,982 --> 01:50:52,486
- What was in it?
- Sentimental things.

908
01:50:52,569 --> 01:50:56,657
A piece of hair from our dog.
Some tickets to the operas

909
01:50:56,740 --> 01:51:00,661
my father had taken me to.
It wasn't stolen for its contents.

910
01:51:00,744 --> 01:51:04,623
It was the tin itself

911
01:51:04,706 --> 01:51:07,334
that was valuable,

912
01:51:07,417 --> 01:51:09,086
what you could do with it.

913
01:51:17,261 --> 01:51:20,180
There's nothing
I can do with this money.

914
01:51:20,264 --> 01:51:23,684
I give it to anything associated
with extermination of Jews,

915
01:51:23,767 --> 01:51:26,353
then to me it seems...

916
01:51:26,436 --> 01:51:29,773
...like absolution, and that's
something I'm neither willing

917
01:51:29,857 --> 01:51:33,569
- nor in a position to grant.
- I was thinking maybe

918
01:51:33,652 --> 01:51:37,531
an organization to encourage literacy.

919
01:51:41,368 --> 01:51:43,871
Good. Good.

920
01:51:43,954 --> 01:51:46,832
Do you know if there
is a Jewish organization?

921
01:51:46,915 --> 01:51:48,667
I'd be surprised if there isn't.

922
01:51:48,750 --> 01:51:52,379
There's a Jewish organization
for everything.

923
01:51:52,463 --> 01:51:55,549
Not that illiteracy
is a very Jewish problem.

924
01:51:57,384 --> 01:52:00,637
Why don't you find out?
Send them the money.

925
01:52:16,862 --> 01:52:18,822
Shall I do it in Hanna's name?

926
01:52:20,824 --> 01:52:22,326
As you think fit.

927
01:52:27,623 --> 01:52:29,416
I'll keep the tin.

928
01:52:34,338 --> 01:52:36,006
Thank you.

929
01:53:27,891 --> 01:53:32,646
- Where are we going?
- I thought you liked surprises.

930
01:53:32,729 --> 01:53:35,858
I do. I do like surprises.

931
01:54:40,130 --> 01:54:42,925
Hanna Schmitz.

932
01:54:47,262 --> 01:54:48,347
Who was she?

933
01:54:50,891 --> 01:54:53,310
That's what I wanted to tell you.

934
01:54:55,479 --> 01:54:57,606
That's why we're here.

935
01:55:05,781 --> 01:55:07,366
So tell me.

936
01:55:19,086 --> 01:55:21,505
I was 15.

937
01:55:24,091 --> 01:55:26,635
I was coming home from school.

938
01:55:28,679 --> 01:55:30,514
I was feeling ill.

939
01:55:31,849 --> 01:55:34,852
And a woman helped me.

